/*!
\page inspection_isfield ISFIELD Test for Existence of a Structure Field

<p>
Section: \ref sec_inspection "Inspection Functions"
\section Usage
Given a structure array, tests to see if that structure
array contains a field with the given name.  The syntax
for its use is
\verbatim
  y = isfield(x,field)
\endverbatim
and returns a logical <tt>1</tt> if <tt>x</tt> has a field with the 
name <tt>field</tt> and a logical <tt>0</tt> if not.  It also returns
a logical <tt>0</tt> if the argument <tt>x</tt> is not a structure array.
\section Example
Here we define a simple struct, and then test for some 
fields

\if FRAGMENT
frag_inspection_isfield_000.m
0
a.foo = 32
a.goo = 64
isfield(a,'goo')
isfield(a,'got')
isfield(pi,'round')
\endif


